{"key":"post-9876986","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9876986</id>\n<content>Granulated gypsum is fine.&amp;nbsp; It will dissolve easily when you wet the substrate. You don't want plain calcium or it will change your pH upward.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Drywall sheeting is your other choice.&amp;nbsp; Get scraps from your local lumber yard or construction sites for free, or simply buy a sheet of it.&amp;nbsp; Rip most of the paper off, and crumble the gypsum between the sheets of paper and use that.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9877023</next>\n<prev>9876148</prev>\n<first>9876148</first>\n<last>9877028</last>\n<when>1235764959</when>\n<utime>02/27/09 10:02 PM</utime>\n</post>"}